{
  "texts": [
    "5128754) was imaged using a diagnostic CT device (GE Revolution Frontier; parameters: 120 kV, 335 mA, 730 ms exposure time, 625 µm pixel size, 5 mm slice thickness, head filter).",
    "Super-Resolution ModelThe training data were created from the preclinical tissue blocks by downscaling the µCT images.",
    "Three datasets with specific imaging resolutions used in the test images and the corresponding 4x magnifications were created, and a separate set of SR models were trained for each dataset (200 µm → 50 µm, 400 µm → 100 µm, 488 µm → 122 µm).",
    "First, µCT images were downscaled to the target resolution, and a Gaussian filter (kernel size = 7, σ = 0.5) was applied to mitigate aliasing artifacts.",
    "The input images were obtained by further downscaling the target images by a factor of four."
  ]
}